  <!-- Things to do -->
  <section class="ed-section">
    <div class="ed-section-head"><h2>While we're there</h2><div class="aside">★ = Lauren's pick</div></div>
    <ul class="ed-place-list">
      <li>
        <div class="name"><a class="ed-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/Balboa+Park+San+Diego+CA" target="_blank">Balboa Park</a><span class="pick">★ Lauren</span></div>
        <div class="addr">San Diego, CA &middot; <a class="ed-link-muted" href="tel:+161****0512">(619) 239-0512</a></div>
        <div class="desc">San Diego's Central Park, bigger. 1,200 acres, 18 museums, gardens, hiking, the San Diego Zoo. Pack a lunch and sit where the planes fly ~50 ft overhead descending into Lindbergh Field. The Prado (1914/15, expanded 1934/35) has the Spanish Colonial architecture from the Panama-California Exposition.</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="name"><a class="ed-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/Cabrillo+National+Monument+1800+Cabrillo+Memorial+Dr+San+Diego+CA+92106" target="_blank">Cabrillo National Monument &amp; Lighthouse</a><span class="pick">★ Lauren</span></div>
        <div class="addr">1800 Cabrillo Memorial Dr, San Diego, CA 92106</div>
        <div class="desc">National monument on the tip of Point Loma ($15-20 entry). 270° views of downtown, Coronado, the north beaches, and the Pacific. Tide pools at the base are open to visitors.</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="name"><a class="ed-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/Windansea+Park+6600+Neptune+Pl+La+Jolla+CA+92037" target="_blank">Windansea Beach</a><span class="pick">★ Lauren's favorite SD beach</span></div>
        <div class="addr">6600 Neptune Pl, La Jolla, CA 92037 &middot; <a class="ed-link-muted" href="tel:+161****8899">(619) 221-8899</a></div>
        <div class="desc">Blue water, yellow-white sand, sandstone caves to explore if the tide allows. Picturesque surf spot with the historic palm-covered surf shack.</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="name"><a class="ed-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/Embarcadero+1492+N+Harbor+Dr+San+Diego+CA+92101" target="_blank">Embarcadero</a></div>
        <div class="addr">1492 N Harbor Dr, San Diego, CA 92101</div>
        <div class="desc">Cruise hub with Seaport Village (seafood, souvenirs), The Headquarters (eateries and boutiques in an old police command post), the USS Midway Museum (aircraft carrier with flight sims and restored planes), and Waterfront Park.</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="name"><a class="ed-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/Marston+House+3525+7th+Ave+San+Diego+CA+92103" target="_blank">Marston House</a></div>
        <div class="addr">3525 7th Ave, San Diego, CA 92103 &middot; <a class="ed-link-muted" href="tel:+161****9327">(619) 297-9327</a></div>
        <div class="desc">Historic Arts &amp; Crafts mansion from 1905.</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="name"><a class="ed-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/Heritage+Park+2454+Heritage+Park+Row+San+Diego+CA+92110" target="_blank">Heritage Park</a></div>
        <div class="addr">2454 Heritage Park Row, San Diego, CA 92110</div>
        <div class="desc">Restored Victorian-era homes from the 1880s-1890s, in Old Town.</div>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

